{
  "stem": "3757.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And follow what I told you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I am worrying about you and [HUNGARIAN], my son.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was-- he was already in the-- they deported, and he was worrying about us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I never had heard about him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But this-- did what he said.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the first thing what the Germans did when they came to Hungary in March 19, 1944, was-- the first rule-- everybody had to take the radios.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Jewish people shouldn't have a radio.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I threw the radio.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I don't know where was it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I had never anybody came to check if I gave the radio.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So I thought, oh, I did this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So that was the last thing that I did.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I didn't take-- [? work ?] the rules.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Give all the money, the jewelry, everything-- I didn't.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "In the meantime, we-- oh, at the building that I used to live was designated as a Jewish house.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "What meant that they put a big yellow star on the-- on the entrance.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we had to wear the yellow star, of course.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we had-- the Jewish people had to move in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So I had a small apartment-- only one living room, and a hall, and a little room for the bed.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So I asked a friend whose husband also was taken to Ukraine to move in with me because I didn't want that they put in a whole family in my small apartment.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So-- and in the meantime, with Irene-- yeah, in the meantime, Irene [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] couldn't stay with-- with us anymore because Jewish people couldn't have a Christian or gentile people in the household.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So she left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And she never took a steady job.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
